\insrsid13321691\charrsid12127175  As is well known, South Africa is a much richer country than any other in Africa and has a significantly larger and more robust publishing and
 education sector (the latter being where many authors work.) But even here, as the above figures show, the RRO system leads to a highly unequal balance of payments to the advantage of richer countries and reinforces existing patterns of dependency. If a 
fully functioning and active RRO were to be established in any other African county, especially a least developed country, the financial inequality would be even greater; such an African RRO would primarily \endash 
 if not exclusively---become a royalty collector for foreign publishers and authors headquartered in rich countries. 
