\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 1.\tab}}\pard \qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\widctlpar\jclisttab\tx360\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls31\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0\pararsid8723256 {
\insrsid7603589 A system of group rights that places traditional knowledge in a permanent condition of cultural protection.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 2.\tab}The use of copyright laws to protect traditional designs and culture from appropriation and misuse.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 3.\tab}Resisting the expansion of TRIPS-plus type legislation at the international level. 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 4.\tab}Utilizing the concept of open source licensing and applying this concept to all areas of creative work and cultural exchange. 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 5.\tab}
Arguing for a strong layer of technology transfer and information exchange at the international level in order to ensure that developing countries do not get left out of technological progress.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 6.\tab}Developing a limited system of rights with short terms for protection but without the lengthy terms inherent in the copyright system.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 7.\tab}Eliminating copyright.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langfenp2057\insrsid7603589 \hich\af56\dbch\af0\loch\f56 8.\tab}Resisting commodification and attempting to retain access to knowledge as a human right and not a commercial right.
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7603589 {\insrsid7603589 
\par As outlined in the first four sections of this dossier, there are serious problems associated with copyright and its application in the global South. While there may be some role for a system of copyright protection, creativity
 and invention certainly happen outside the boundaries of copyright law. 
\par 
\par A system of copyright allows for creative works to be privatised and primarily benefits the owners of copyrights. The owners of copyright are often not the same as the original crea
tors of the artistic work. Take the example of classic American jazz artists. Many of these talented musicians, responsible for creating one of America\rquote 
s most original musical forms, were paid flat rates for their most important contributions to this music
. The bulk of the profits produced by jazz artists went to the labels and producers with many of the most talented musicians dying penniless. Copyrights did nothing to encourage innovation and creativity in this example, but rather established a system of
 
exploitation in which those who create are not likely to benefit from their creations. Furthermore, copyright makes it difficult to build upon the earlier work of other jazz musicians by privatising the music and requiring licences to use even the smalles
t
 portions. Such monopolization of music is a barrier to the creation of new works instead of facilitating new creation. The same type of problems will exist as countries throughout the global South come to see music as a form of property instead of a cult
ural treasure.}{\cs18\super\insrsid7603589 \chftn {\footnote \pard\plain \s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid12127175 \f56\fs20\lang2057\langfe2057\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp2057 {
\cs18\super\insrsid8483307\charrsid12127175 \chftn }{\insrsid8483307\charrsid12127175  Anthony McCann maps the enclosure of Irish folk music in his dissertation, }{\insrsid8483307\charrsid983116 \lquote 
Beyond the Commons: The Expansion of the Irish Music Rights Organization, the Elimination of Uncertainty, and the Politics of Enclosure}{\i\insrsid8483307\charrsid983116 \rquote  }{\insrsid8483307 (}{\insrsid8483307\charrsid12127175 2002. }{
\insrsid8483307 Available }{\insrsid8483307\charrsid1267907 http://www.beyondthecommons.com/beyondthecommons.html}{\insrsid8483307 ).}}}{\insrsid7603589  
\par 
\par Instead of assuming the western system spurs innovation, it is important to recognize that most of the important innovation and creativity happens during relatively open and less regulated eras whe
re people work for the common good instead of individual property rights.}{\cs18\super\insrsid7603589 \chftn {\footnote \pard\plain \s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid12127175 
