\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8723256 \f56\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp2057 {\insrsid7603589\charrsid9309490 
\par On the other hand, and this is the more critical point , this group and its draft A2K treaty start \endash  and essentially end \endash 
 by funnelling all access questions through a traditional copyright lens, albeit a slightly more liberal and pro-user friendly version. For example, instituting a more liberal US \lquote fair use\rquote  or UK \lquote fair dealing\rquote 
 regime in the South is viewed as }{\insrsid8723256\charrsid9309490 the principle }{\insrsid7603589\charrsid9309490 and }{\insrsid8723256\charrsid9309490 essential answer }{\insrsid7603589\charrsid9309490 
for overcoming access problems in the South. Traditional privileged actors in copyright discourse, such as \lquote authors\rquote 
 retain a privileged place (as they do with Creative Commons licences; see section 5.9 of this dossier). Well-known copyright barriers affecting, for example, the visually impaired (e.g. how any type of reproduction needed to produce materials in an acces
sible format is necessarily an infringement of copyright) are }{\insrsid8723256\charrsid9309490 not}{\insrsid7603589\charrsid9309490 
 challenged head-on. This document avoids suggesting that changing the format of a document to allow access should legally }{\insrsid8723256\charrsid9309490 not}{\insrsid7603589\charrsid9309490 
